    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1061"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1061">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 894.4054/17</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Japanese Embassy has been informed by the Japanese Consul at Seattle that
                    seven “picture brides” arrived per S. S. <hi rend="italic">Canada Maru</hi> on
                    the 26th of May and are actually detained at their own expense at the immigrant
                    station at that port until the presentation of the certified copies of the
                    notification of marriage which they were not provided with.</p>
                <p>The Embassy begs to request the State Department to be good enough to see its
                    way, as soon as may be possible, to arrange for their temporary admittance on
                    the assurance by the Japanese Consul for the presentation by the parties
                    concerned of the necessary documents at a later date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial Japanese Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
